  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6594.15 sitting directly between the massive negative gamma wall at 6590 (-14.3B) and positive gamma wall at 6605 (+15.8B), dealers are in active hedging mode - buying the dip toward 6590 and preparing to sell any push toward 6605. The BREAKOUT regime with -20.2B total GEX means dealers will amplify moves, creating a high-tension spring effect in this tight 15-point range. Key inflection is 6605 - a break above triggers dealer selling and opens upside, while failure here and drift toward 6590 gets dealer buying support but with amplified volatility.\n\nThe gex_surge event combined with 54% 1-minute change signals rapidly shifting positioning that could unleash explosive moves in either direction from this compressed range.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent whipsaws between 6590-6605 until one level decisively breaks.",
